description:
At Genmab, we are dedicated to building extra\[not]ordinary® futures, together, by developing antibody products and groundbreaking, knock\-your\-socks\-off KYSO antibody medicines® that change lives and the future of cancer treatment and serious diseases. We strive to create, champion and maintain a global workplace where individuals’ unique contributions are valued and drive innovative solutions to meet the needs of our patients, care partners, families and employees.





Our people are compassionate, candid, and purposeful, and our business is innovative and rooted in science. We believe that being proudly authentic and determined to be our best is essential to fulfilling our purpose. Yes, our work is incredibly serious and impactful, but we have big ambitions, bring a ton of care to pursuing them, and have a lot of fun while doing so.





Does this inspire you and feel like a fit? Then we would love to have you join us!





Genmab is strengthening its presence in Europe and expanding its commercial capabilities to bring innovative medicines to more patients. As pioneers in antibody biology and innovation, we are seeking a driven and talented individual to help deliver our cutting\-edge oncology treatments to patients across Italy. If you’re passionate about oncology, bring experience from both large pharmaceutical organizations and nimble biotech environments, and with a deep expertise of the Italian market access \& pricing landscape, we want to hear from you!


**The Role**


Genmab is preparing to launch a new innovation in cervical cancer in Europe. In this role, you will lead development of the Italian Market Access strategy for the company’s oncology pipeline. Specifically, the Market access strategy, pricing and public affairs director will lead efforts in assessing and communicating to internal and external stakeholders the market access requirements of Italy for oncology, contributing to and shaping the overall value strategy for our brands throughout lifecycle. The position will drive development of local market access strategy, delivery of HTA submissions, and lead P\&R negotiations. In this role, the director will have also to develop and implement a strong public affairs plan in collaboration with the GM (General Manager).


**Responsibilities**


* Identify, analyse, develop, and implement recommendations and strategies regarding P\&R policy and challenges important to company’s product portfolio;
* Analyse, synthesize, and translate technical P\&R information, including coverage and reimbursement policies, into meaningful decision points, recommendations, and strategic tactics;
* Champion the P\&R requirements for Italian Commercial Operations throughout commercialization and ensure alignment between all stakeholders internally as to prioritized needs;
* Contribute to strategy discussions and communication efforts with relevant external stakeholders including key government agencies and organizations;
* Partner in development of European and global value access \& pricing deliverables, working in close collaboration with European and global colleagues and external vendors as needed;
* Drive development of Italian market access deliverables including HTA submissions; local evidence generation plans; negotiation strategies, and country\-level regional and local market access tactics to secure reimbursement;
* Develop HTA payer and advocacy engagement plans and other external experts;
* Maintain alignment of local market access strategy to European and Global Market Access Strategy; establish pricing position within EU Price Brand;
* Collaborate closely with relevant internal stakeholders, including Marketing, Medical Affairs, Regulatory, etc.



**Requirements**


* 10 to 15 years of experience within the field of Market Access \& pricing. Experience in Health Economics and Outcomes Research is a plus;
* Strong network of relevant stakeholders in Italy;
* Strong knowledge of the market access \& pricing landscape;
* Strong oncology market knowledge from a commercial and clinical studies perspective;
* Excellent communication and negotiation skills;
* Business fluency in English;
* Fluency in local language is a must .

**In order to be considered please apply with a English resume.**



The proposed gross annual base salary range for this position, in the primary location, based on a full time schedule is:


EUR0,00\-0,00\&\#xa;  



The final salary offer will depend on several factors, including your skills, qualifications, and experience.


In addition to base salary, this position is eligible to additional forms of compensation, such as discretionary bonuses and long\-term incentives.


When you join Genmab, you become a part of a culture that supports your physical, financial, social, and emotional well\-being. Our benefits include, but are not limited to:


* Pension
* Health insurance and wellness benefits
* Paid time off
* Employee support programs




Further details on compensation and benefits will be provided during the recruitment process.







**About Genmab**


Genmab is an international biotechnology company with a core purpose to improve the lives of patients through innovative and differentiated antibody therapeutics. For 25 years, its hard\-working, innovative and collaborative team has invented next\-generation antibody technology platforms and harnessed translational, quantitative and data sciences, resulting in a proprietary pipeline including bispecific T\-cell engagers, antibody\-drug conjugates, next\-generation immune checkpoint modulators and effector function\-enhanced antibodies. By 2030, Genmab’s vision is to transform the lives of people with cancer and other serious diseases with Knock\-Your\-Socks\-Off (KYSO®) antibody medicines.





Established in 1999, Genmab is headquartered in Copenhagen, Denmark with international presence across North America, Europe and Asia Pacific. For more information, please visit Genmab.com and follow us on LinkedIn and X.





Genmab is committed to protecting your personal data and privacy. Please see our privacy policy for handling your data in connection with your application on our website Job Applicant Privacy Notice (genmab.com).





Please note that if you are applying for a position in the Netherlands, Genmab’s policy for all permanently budgeted hires in NL is initially to offer a fixed\-term employment contract for a year, if the employee performs well and if the business conditions do not change, renewal for an indefinite term may be considered after the contract.

Take a step forward and let Edenred surprise you.


Every day, we deliver innovative solutions to improve the life of millions of people, connecting employees, companies, and merchants all around the world.


We know there are hundred ways for you to grow. With us, you will expand your skills in a multicultural, challenging, and dynamic environment.


**Dare to join Edenred and get ready to thrive in a global company that will offer you endless opportunities.**

Edenred is all about meritocracy. You come as you are, and you contribute. Indeed, the Edenred Group recognizes, recruits and develops all talents and singularities.


We are committed to preventing all forms of discrimination and to providing all our candidates with equal opportunities regardless of their gender and gender expression, disability, origin, religious belief and sexual orientation or any other criteria.


**YOU WILL VIBE WITH US**

We are looking for a ***Demand Manager*** with strong expertise in business process analysis and optimization, capable of understanding how business processes are supported by applications, systems, and data flows across the organization.


The role will act as the primary bridge between Business and Technology stakeholders, ensuring that business needs are properly understood, translated into valuable initiatives, and delivered through effective IT solutions.


A strong focus will be placed on ***process discovery, process mapping, and continuous improvement,*** identifying opportunities to simplify, standardize, automate, and enhance business operations through technology.


He/she will be in charge of:


**Business Process Analysis and Improvement**

* Analyze end\-to\-end business processes and their interaction with applications, systems, integrations, and data flows;
* Map and document AS\-IS and TO\-BE processes using BPMN 2\.0, identifying inefficiencies, bottlenecks, redundancies, and opportunities for simplification, standardization, and automation;
* Collaborate with business stakeholders to redesign processes and improve operational performance through technology\-enabled solutions.

**Demand Management and Prioritization**

* Collect, assess, and qualify business requests and improvement opportunities, ensuring alignment with strategic objectives and process evolution;
* Build business cases by evaluating benefits, costs, risks, and expected business impact;
* Support prioritization activities, balancing business value, available capacity, and architectural constraints, while maintaining the demand backlog and roadmap.

**Requirements and Solution Definition**

* Translate business and process needs into clear functional and non\-functional requirements;
* Support solution design activities with IT teams, architects, and external partners;
* Ensure requirements traceability throughout the initiative lifecycle.

**Stakeholder Management and Delivery Readiness**

* Act as the primary interface between Business and Technology stakeholders, facilitating alignment and decision\-making;
* Support scope definition, MVP identification, acceptance criteria, and UAT activities;
* Ensure business readiness and adoption of delivered solutions.

**Value Realization and Governance**

* Define success criteria, KPIs, and expected benefits for initiatives;
* Monitor benefits realization, process performance, and solution effectiveness after go\-live;
* Support governance activities, ensuring compliance with internal standards, policies, and risk management requirements.

**WE WILL VIBE WITH YOU**

***Passion for customer, respect, imagination, simplicity and entrepreneurial spirit are*** the values we look for in our people. If you recognize yourself and want to get involved in a stimulating and multinational environment, send us your application and become an ***Edenreder*** too!


* Minimum 4\+ years of experience in Demand Management, Business Analysis, Process Improvement, or IT Project Management within multinational organizations or consulting firms;
* Strong experience in business process analysis and modeling, including BPMN 2\.0, process mapping, AS\-IS / TO\-BE analysis, value stream mapping, and continuous improvement methodologies;
* Proven ability to analyze how business processes are supported by enterprise applications, workflows, integrations, and data flows;
* Solid business analysis skills, including requirements elicitation, user stories, use cases, process metrics, and requirements traceability;
* Good understanding of enterprise applications and digital transformation initiatives;
* Solid Project Management capabilities, preferably within Agile environments;
* Excellent stakeholder management, communication, facilitation, and influencing skills;
* Fluent English, both written and spoken, with experience working in international environments;
* Master's degree in Management Engineering, Economics, Information Systems, or related fields.

**OTHER DETAILS**

* Permanent Contract
* CCNL Commercio
* Gross Annual Salary (RAL) starting from € 46\.000, determined on the basis of objective and transparent criteria, including professional experience gained, specialized technical skills, the level of autonomy and responsibility required, and alignment with the company's compensation and job classification framework
* Performance bonus in line with the company's incentive plan

* Smart\-working (10 days/month)
* ️ Ticket Restaurant®
* ️ Welfare Plan
* Comprehensive health benefits, including supplementary medical insurance, accident protection and life coverage

**EQUAL OPPORTUNITIES AND HIRING PROCESS**

Edenred fosters an inclusive workplace grounded in equal opportunity, with recruitment and career development processes based on fairness, transparency, and merit.


Candidates are assessed without discrimination on the basis of gender, age, ethnicity, social background, nationality, sexual orientation, personal or religious beliefs, disability, or any other legally protected characteristic.


**Apply now and Vibe with Us!**
